From 0b036c348c388f8466ccbf8a507f737771569853 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 11:35:28 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 13/14] chronium: per-profile UA Client Hints via
 ChromeContentBrowserClient::GetUserAgentMetadata override
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Plan §5 #6 'Navigator + UA-CH' and §0.2 root cause #2 'UA / UA-CH
mismatch HTTP vs JS' — the highest-leverage Google-detect win short
of TLS/JA3 work. The override is a single seam: Chromium fans the
returned UserAgentMetadata out to every Sec-CH-UA-* request header
in the network service AND to navigator.userAgentData /
userAgentData.getHighEntropyValues() on the JS side, so one hook
fixes both.

FingerprintProfile::UserAgentMetadata
  Parses the profile JSON's 'user_agent_data' dict into a
  blink::UserAgentMetadata:
   - brand_version_list      <- 'brands' array
   - brand_full_version_list <- 'full_version_list' array
   - platform, platform_version, architecture, bitness, model,
     mobile, wow64           <- their respective JSON keys
   - full_version            <- first entry's version from
                                full_version_list (matches what
                                Chromium derives internally)
  Returns std::nullopt when the field is absent, signalling
  ChromeContentBrowserClient to fall back to the embedder default.

ChromeContentBrowserClient::GetUserAgentMetadata
  Plugs the profile-provided metadata in when a profile is loaded,
  before delegating to embedder_support::GetUserAgentMetadata.

Pair this with the existing patch 0006 --user-agent attach: that
patch handled the legacy User-Agent string and JS
navigator.userAgent; this patch handles every modern Sec-CH-UA-*
plus navigator.userAgentData. They share their source (the JSON
profile) so consistency between the two is enforced by config —
if you set 'user_agent' to a Windows UA and 'user_agent_data' to
macOS, the mismatch is visible in the JSON itself.

Verified on profile B (macOS user_agent + macOS user_agent_data):
  JS getHighEntropyValues   -> platform 'macOS', platformVersion
                               '14.5.0', architecture 'arm',
                               bitness '64'
  HTTP User-Agent header    -> 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac
                               OS X 10_15_7) ...'
  HTTP Sec-Ch-Ua-Platform   -> '"macOS"'
  HTTP Sec-Ch-Ua-Mobile     -> '?0'
  HTTP Sec-Ch-Ua            -> '"Chromium";v="130", "Google
                               Chrome";v="130", "Not?A_Brand"
                               ;v="99"'

Files touched:
- chrome/browser/fingerprint/fingerprint_profile.{h,cc}
- chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc
